"title": "7021: church, OT anticipations of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7021",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>As the people of God, the Christian church is continuous with Israel. The OT provides important anticipations of the church.</p>\n<h2>OT terms for the people of God</h2>\n<h3>The descendants of Abraham</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:7\">2CH 20:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:8-Isa41:9\">ISA 41:8–41:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:16\">ROM 4:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:7\">GAL 3:7</a> <em>“children of Abraham” in the NT refers to those who, like Abraham, put their faith in God</em></p>\n<h3>The saints</h3>\n<p>The term for <code>saints'' means</code>set apart for God'', ``made holy'', and is the most frequently used NT term for Christians:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:9\">1SA 2:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:41\">2CH 6:41</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps132:9\">PSA 132:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:3\">PSA 16:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:23\">PSA 31:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:18\">DAN 7:18</a></p>\n<h3>The assembly</h3>\n<p><code>assembly'' means</code>a community gathered together in response to God's call to serve and worship him''. Its NT equivalents include the synagogue and the church:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:5\">PSA 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:32\">PSA 107:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:1\">PSA 149:1</a></p>\n<h2>The scope of the OT people of God</h2>\n<h3>Israel as God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:7\">EXO 6:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5-Exod19:6\">EXO 19:5–19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:12\">LEV 26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:22\">JER 30:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:28\">EZK 36:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:23\">HOS 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>Not all Israelites are God's people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:6-Rom9:7\">ROM 9:6–9:7</a></strong> <em>Even within Israel there are believers and unbelievers.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:8\">EZR 9:8</a> <em>Those Israelites who believed were sometimes called “a remnant”</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:9\">ISA 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:11\">ISA 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:16\">ISA 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:3\">JER 23:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:22\">EZK 14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:12\">MIC 2:12</a></p>\n<h3>God's people included non-Israelites</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa2:2-Isa2:3\">ISA 2:2–2:3</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:1-Mic4:2\">MIC 4:1–4:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:38\">EXO 12:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:48-Exod12:49\">EXO 12:48–12:49</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:12\">DEU 31:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:10-Ruth4:11\">RUT 4:10–4:11</a></p>\n<h2>The formation of the OT people of God</h2>\n<h3>God's people are formed through God's promises</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:2\">GEN 12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:5\">GEN 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:5-Gen17:6\">GEN 17:5–17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:17-Gen22:18\">GEN 22:17–22:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:7\">EXO 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>God's people are chosen and called</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:6\">DEU 7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:13\">1CH 16:13</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:6\">PSA 105:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:12\">PSA 33:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:5\">EZK 20:5</a></p>\n<h3>God's people have been redeemed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:6\">DEU 5:6</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:2\">EXO 20:2</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:6\">EXO 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:4\">EXO 19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:6\">EZK 20:6</a></p>\n<h3>God formed a covenant with his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:8\">EXO 24:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:5\">EXO 19:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:10\">EXO 34:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:27\">EXO 34:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:13\">DEU 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:1\">JDG 2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:31\">JER 31:31</a></p>\n<h2>OT images of the people of God</h2>\n<h3>As God's bride</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:2\">JER 2:2</a></strong> <em>This OT image is taken up in the many references to Jesus Christ as the bridegroom and the church as his bride.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:5\">ISA 62:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:16\">HOS 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:19-Hos2:20\">HOS 2:19–2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:27\">EPH 5:25–5:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:2\">REV 21:2</a></p>\n<h3>As God's vine</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1-Isa5:7\">ISA 5:1–5:7</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:8\">PSA 80:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:21\">JER 2:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:5-Ezek17:6\">EZK 17:5–17:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:10\">EZK 19:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:1\">HOS 10:1</a></p>\n<h3>As God's flock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:7\">PSA 95:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps74:1\">PSA 74:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:20\">PSA 77:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps100:3\">PSA 100:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:16\">ZEC 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:31\">MAT 26:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech13:7\">ZEC 13:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:32\">LUK 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:16\">JHN 10:16</a>ACT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:28-John20:29\">20:28–20:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2-1Pet5:3\">1PE 5:2–5:3</a></p>\n<h3>As God's inheritance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:20\">DEU 4:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:9\">PSA 28:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:12\">PSA 33:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:25\">ISA 19:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal3:17\">MAL 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>As God's family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos3:1-Amos3:2\">AMO 3:1–3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:22-Exod4:23\">EXO 4:22–4:23</a> <em>Israel was sometimes called God's “firstborn son” as well as his children</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:31\">DEU 1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:6\">DEU 32:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:13\">PSA 103:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:2\">ISA 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:9\">ISA 30:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos11:1\">HOS 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:10\">MAL 2:10</a></p>\n<h2>Requirements of the people of God</h2>\n<h3>To obey God's word</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:1\">DEU 5:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:3\">EXO 24:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:1-Deut6:3\">DEU 6:1–6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut13:4\">DEU 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:7\">JOS 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:22\">1SA 15:22</a></p>\n<h3>To remember their redemption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:15\">DEU 5:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:18\">DEU 7:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut15:15\">DEU 15:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:12\">DEU 16:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:5\">PSA 105:5</a></p>\n<h3>To commemorate their redemption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:25-Exod12:27\">EXO 12:25–12:27</a></strong> <em>The focus of Israel's commemoration of their redemption was the Passover, which is one of the ceremonies lying behind the Lord's Supper.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:2-Num9:3\">NUM 9:2–9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:1\">DEU 16:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:14-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:14–22:20</a></p>\n<h3>To love God wholeheartedly</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:5\">DEU 6:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:12\">DEU 10:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:1\">DEU 11:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:9\">DEU 19:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:11\">JOS 23:11</a></p>\n<h2>The marks of the people of God</h2>\n<h3>Circumcision as a mark of God's people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:10-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:10–17:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:3\">LEV 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:16\">DEU 10:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:6\">DEU 30:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer4:4\">JER 4:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:27\">ROM 2:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11\">COL 2:11</a></p>\n<h3>The presence of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod25:8\">EXO 25:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:15-Exod33:16\">EXO 33:15–33:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod40:35\">EXO 40:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:33-Num10:36\">NUM 10:33–10:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:14\">2CH 5:14</a></p>",
